{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.33",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 33,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 33 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:1",
      "text": "No evil will happen to him who fears the Lord, but in trials once and again he will deliver him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:2",
      "text": "A wise man will not hate the law, but he who is a hypocrite about it is like a boat in a storm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:3",
      "text": "A man of understanding will put his trust in the law. And the law is faithful to him, as when one asks a divine oracle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:4",
      "text": "Prepare your speech, and so you will be heard. Bind up instruction, and make your answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:5",
      "text": "The heart of a fool is like a cartwheel. His thoughts are like a rolling axle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:6",
      "text": "A stallion horse is like a mocking friend. He neighs under every one who sits upon him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:7",
      "text": "Why does one day excel another, when all the light of every day in the year is from the sun?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:8",
      "text": "They were distinguished by the Lord’s knowledge, and he varied seasons and feasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:9",
      "text": "Some of them he exalted and hallowed, and some of them he has made ordinary days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:10",
      "text": "And all men are from the ground. Adam was created from dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:11",
      "text": "In the abundance of his knowledge the Lord distinguished them, and made their ways different.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:12",
      "text": "Some of them he blessed and exalted, and some of them he made holy and brought near to himself. Some of them he cursed and brought low, and overthrew them from their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:13",
      "text": "As the clay of the potter in his hand, all his ways are according to his good pleasure, so men are in the hand of him who made them, to give to them according to his judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:14",
      "text": "Good is the opposite of evil, and life is the opposite of death; so the sinner is the opposite of the godly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:15",
      "text": "Look upon all the works of the Most High like this, they come in pairs, one against another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:16",
      "text": "I was the last on watch, like one who gleans after the grape gatherers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:17",
      "text": "By the Lord’s blessing I arrived before them, and filled my winepress like one who gathers grapes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:18",
      "text": "Consider that I labored not for myself alone, but for all those who seek instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:19",
      "text": "Hear me, you great men of the people, and listen with your ears, you rulers of the congregation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:20",
      "text": "To son and wife, to brother and friend, don’t give power over yourself while you live, and don’t give your goods to another, lest you regret it and must ask for them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:21",
      "text": "While you still live and breath is in you, don’t give yourself over to anybody.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:22",
      "text": "For it is better that your children should ask from you than that you should look to the hand of your children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:23",
      "text": "Excel in all your works. Don’t bring a stain on your honor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:24",
      "text": "In the day that you end the days of your life, in the time of death, distribute your inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:25",
      "text": "Fodder, a stick, and burdens are for a donkey. Bread, discipline, and work are for a servant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:26",
      "text": "Set your slave to work, and you will find rest. Leave his hands idle, and he will seek liberty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:27",
      "text": "Yoke and whip will bow the neck. For an evil slave there are racks and tortures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:28",
      "text": "Send him to labor, that he not be idle, for idleness teaches much mischief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:29",
      "text": "Set him to work, as is fit for him. If he doesn’t obey, make his fetters heavy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:30",
      "text": "Don’t be excessive toward any. Do nothing unjust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:31",
      "text": "If you have a slave, treat him like yourself, because you have bought him with blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:32",
      "text": "If you have a slave, treat him like yourself. For like your own soul, you will need him. If you treat him ill, and he departs and runs away,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.33.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 33:33",
      "text": "which way will you go to seek him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
